peMA.Aposticha1.mode = misc_en_US_dedes.Mode2
peMA.Aposticha1.melody = he.a.m2_en_US_dedes.OteEkTouXylou.incipit
peMA.Aposticha1.text = "Savior, when as God You rose from death, * You gave to the Myrrh-bearing women great joy, O Logos, and said, * \"Since I have not yet ascended to my Father on high, * do not touch me now, but instead go quickly and tell my * friends, 'Behold, He goes before you into Galilee.'\" * Later, You appeared to them gathered * in the upper room, and You gave them * the all-holy Spirit when You breathed on them."

peMA.Aposticha2.mode = misc_en_US_dedes.Mode2
peMA.Aposticha2.melody = he.a.m2_en_US_dedes.OteEkTouXylou.incipit
peMA.Aposticha2.text = "Hearing the Myrrh-bearing women's words * and their proclamation of Christ's resurrection from the dead, * not believing them, the Mystics went to see for themselves. * And they saw in the sepulcher the shroud and the napkin, * but they did not see the One whom they were looking for. * Later, they would have a full knowledge * of the Resurrection and preach it * to all nations as Apostles in the world."

peMA.Aposticha3.mode = misc_en_US_dedes.Mode2
peMA.Aposticha3.melody = he.a.m2_en_US_dedes.OteEkTouXylou.incipit
peMA.Aposticha3.text = "Christ the Lord has shone forth from the tomb * beautiful and radiant, showing us unapproachable light. * Hades has been overthrown; Satan has disappeared. * All the ends of the earth rejoice, creation is dancing. * And the Church of Christ is honoring the memory * of the wise disciple St. Joseph * and the holy Myrrh-bearing women, * singing festive hymns today extolling them."

